Content: bots usually act as marketmaker, they only post orders in the orderbook, they don't fill them... so the price is not made by the bots

Author: c2k#4915
Content: @cipi why do you say the bots only post bids and offers but never get filled?

Author: cipi#4502
Content: i meant they don't actively fill orders, they are waiting for others to fill them...  that is the way i do it, but i think most other bots do the same

Author: c2k#4915
Content:
ok, just trying to understand how it works in crypto bots.
so youre saying theyre passive?...sit on the bid and wait to be hit or sit on the offer and wait to be lifted, but never actually cross the spread and "cause" the trade?

Author: c2k#4915
Content: in equities bots act similarly, especially in tight spreads, because the ECN's pay them to provide liquidity. IE, a "maker" who provides liquidity gets paid ~0.002 while a "taker" of liquidity has to pay ~0.003 .

Author: c2k#4915
Content: but a liquidity provider in crypto doesnt get "paid" a rebate for providing that liquidity, correct?

Author: cipi#4502
Content: no, Binance doesn't pay the makers, the only difference is that you pay a smaller fee as a maker
